8) Morgulduin<br />
9) threats    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">So yes, Dwarves are everywhere. They choke, they draw, they win fights and they are generally REALLY frickin&#39; good. Well, whats more ridiculous than a deck that draws lots of cards and wins all it&#39;s fights? Why, a 17 base strength companion, thats what!<br />
<br />
The fellowship has won me 2 tournaments, one with the Shadow posted and one with a larger Moria stoppy deck thats been posted before. While there aren&#39;t as many pumps as I&#39;d like, the size of the deck and the number of things I&#39;m trying to fit in there have a lot to with that. Terrible and Evil handles Grima, W and any Nazgul too big for Durin 3 to eat and also doubles as (BAD) swarm prevention. The fellowship gives mucho pool but you&#39;ll be surprised at the amount of punishment it can deal out as well as handle. <br />
<br />
The shadow side is slightly standard Morcs, thanks to C. Tubman on the tip-off that these guys are good now :P<br />
<br />
I know this is a pitiful post, the strategy section sucks balls, but I&#39;m tired :P<br />
